{
  "texts": [
    "A diverse range of literature has been explored on VSR techniques to avoid the impact of background noise on speech recognition performance (Petridis et al., 2017 (Petridis et al.,, 2018b;; Martinez et al., 2020; Ma et al., 2021 Ma et al.,, 2022 Ma et al.,, 2023;; Kim et al., 2022; Cheng et al., 2023b; Kim et al., 2023 Kim et al.,, 2024a,b;,b; Yeo et al., 2024b,c,d).",
    "Audio-visual speech recognition integrates both audio and visual modalities as input, combining the strengths of ASR and VSR techniques to enhance the robustness and performance of speech recognition systems, particularly in noisy environments.",
    "Early AVSR models (Noda et al., 2015; Huang and Kingsbury, 2013; Mroueh et al., 2015; Stewart et al., 2013) established the foundation for multimodal speech recognition, demonstrating the effectiveness of fusing visual features such as lip movements with audio signals.",
    "Advancements in AVSR (Petridis et al., 2018a; Shi et al., 2022b; Hong et al., 2022 Hong et al.,, 2023)) have been fueled by improvements in both data availability (Chung et al., 2017; Afouras et al., 2018b) and model architectures (Vaswani, 2017; Gulati et al., 2020).",
    "Selfsupervised learning has also played a crucial role in advancing AVSR (Shi et al., 2022a; Lian et al., 2023; Haliassos et al., 2024b,a) to further enhance performance."
  ]
}